reviews.review_text:
No need to mainline This show will go straight to your pleasure center regardless.

Thanks for yet another gem Charlie
Fox 72' Gr8  show gr8 set list.darkstar is hot. Recommended 72'

Phenomenal It seems that this show is overlooked a bit, which is understandable due to the many amazing performances from '72.  But I think Playin' > Dark Star > Dew > Playin' should get a bit more love and respect that it does.  The transition to Playin' Reprise from Dew is unique and outstanding - perfectly executed with powerful energy.  Powerhouse show in Saint Louis.

Bobby tone Always noticed Bob's tone in this show has a unique extra "bite" of distortion that works well to highlight his style.  I don't know about such settings but maybe a guitar player can explain what the effect is. I assume it is his 1972 era ES just with some adjustments for the night. Good stuff.

"Dark Star" themes What's that familiar sounding theme in Lesh's bass solo ('Philo Stomp')? Is that a "Feelin' Groovy" tucked in there, too? 

Also, was that the first time they veered off "Morning Dew" into a different song? 

5-Star Show; 5-Star Recording!
